This paper deals with the design and decoding of network codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The paper also discusses the use of sparse codes, which is a topic of interest in the data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI) communities. Finally, the paper proposes a low-complexity decoder, which is relevant to the computer communications (cs.CC) community.
